  nextSceneButton: {fileID: 0}
  autoNextSceneName: FourthAct
  introDialogueLines:
  - 'The crowd falls silent, as a tall figure approaches the bonfire.

'
  - "Brother Garrick lowers his head respectfully \u2013 the others follow."
  - "You try to get a better look at the stranger\u2019s face, but their hood hinders
    you from\r\ndoing so."
  - He stands still for a moment. Then he raises his Hand.
  - "\u201CMy brothers and sisters.\u201D"
  - "\u201CTonight we welcome another lost soul.\u201D"
  - " \u201CA jester who arrived troubled by hardship.\u201D"
  - "\u201CJust like many of us once did.\u201D"
  - Several people in the crowd nod.
  - "\u201CThe world beyond these woods\u2026 its cruel\u2026\u201D"
  - "\u201CThey believe in taking everything you\u2019ve got to give - Your money,
    your time, your\r\ndignity.\u201D\r\n"
  - "\u201CBut here \u2013 no soul is discarded or forgotten. No soul shall suffer
    alone.\u201D"
  - ' *applause*'
  - The crowd murmurs in agreement.
  - A strange warmth spreads through the gathering.
  - And for the first time since being dismissed from court, you feel like you belong.
  - '"Tonight we share food."'
  - '"We share stories."'
  - '"And we give thanks for another soul finding their way home."

'
  - Several faces turn toward you.
  - ' Some smiling.'
  - Some merely watching.
  - '"You are welcome here."'
  - '"May the Flesh embrace you."'
  - '"May the Flesh embrace you."'
  - 'The stranger turns around and leaves, while all the others start to embrace
    in

    conversations.'
  - " \u201CI should talk to some of the others, before going to bed.\u201D\r\n"
  afterNoteDialogueLines: []
  choices: []
  endingLines:
  - You take one last look around the gathering.
  - A yawn escapes your lips, and you feel your eyes get heavy.
  - "\u201CI should go to sleep now...\u201D"
  - 'As you turn to your cabin, the bonfire crackles behind you and several members

    nod
    at you as you pass.'
  - You reach your door.
  - '*Creakkk*'
  - Your room greets you with the same stillness as before.
  - Before taking off your garment, you reach into your pocket.
  - The cards.
  - "\u201CMaybe I will find out more about these cards tomorrow.\u201D"
  - You extinguish the candle and snuggle into your new bed.
  - You close your eyes...
  - ... and you doze of.
